<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@EM{{@HI{{yara}}}} is a particle that joins nouns in a non-exhastive list. This usage is similar to that of <a href="grammar-particle-ya.html">@HI{{ya}}</a>,
<a href="grammar-particle-toka.html">@HI{{toka}}</a> and <a href="grammar-particle-dano.html">@HI{{dano}}</a>.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{country}}no@KJ{{person}}tachiha,@FG{{@KJ{{war^contend}}:sensou}}@EM{{yara}},@KT{{infure}}@EM{{yara}}de@KJ{{large^unusual}}deshoune.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What with the war, inflation and so on, the people of that country must be having a hard time.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@EM{{@HI{{yara}}}} is a particle that can be used with words of opposite meaning. This usage is similar to that of <a href="grammar-particle-ka.html#alternative">@HI{{ka}}</a>,
but @EM{{yara}} iss softer in tone.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{pa-texi-}}ni@KJ{{going}}ku@EM{{yara}}@KJ{{going}}kanai@EM{{yara}},hakkirishite@KJ{{below}}sai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please make it clear whether or not you are going to the party.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@EM{{@HI{{yara}}}} is a particle that can be usd with interrogatives to express uncertainty.
(@HI{{wakaranai}}, if not explicitly included, is understood).


<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{dog}}hadokohe@KJ{{going}}tta@EM{{yara}},wakaranaidesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I have no idea where that dog went.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
At the end of a sentence, @EM{{@HI{{yara}}}} is a particle that marks a rhetorical question with negative implications.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{come^year}}hadon'na@KJ{{year}}ninaru@EM{{yara}}@JDOTS6{{}}}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder what kind of year next year will be.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

